data.title: Amy’s Childhood
data.meta_description: This is just a short excerpt for the about page.
data.text:
Amy was born in the Chace House Hospital on the 14th of September 1983.She was born into a Jewish family.

Amy lived in the London’s Southgate area where she lived with her mum Janis who was a pharmacist, her father Mitchell who was a taxi driver and a window cleaner and her older brother Alex.

Amy grew up around music all of her life with her uncles who were professional jazz musicians and her grandmother being a singer. As well as attending Osidge primary school Amy attended Sunday school which she didn’t like. Amy had no interest in her religion or attending a synagogue she attended once a year out of respect.

As Amy grew older her passion for music grew and at the age of 10 Amy and her friends set up a rap band called Sweet and sour the band was short lived. Amy attended Sylvia Young Theatre School at the age of 12. Receiving her own guitar at the age of 13 was what started Amy’s love and passion for song writing.

Amy’s childhood was a happy on until Amy’s parents split and left Amy staying with her mum during the week and her dad and his girlfriend at weekends. At the age of 14 Amy was expelled from theater school for not Appling herself and her rebellious behavior started to affect her music. Her rebellious ways continued to to grow with her through
